fields.transit: We love to walk and cycle around the city. Both are very easy from where our flat is. There is a public bicycle hire point (costing £2 per day) only 30 meters from our front door. There are three different train lines you can reach from our place. Firstly, the London Overground route (via Hoxton and Haggerston stations) which is an orbital track taking you up to Islington and Hampstead, or down to Aldgate and New Cross. The nearest Northern Line station is Old Street which takes you to up Euston and Camden or down to Kennington and Clapham. Finally, the Central Line is accessible via Bethnal Green station and can be used to take you into Oxford Street and Notting Hill. There are also tons of buses from either Kingsland Road or Hackney Road. They are cheap and very reliable and can take you to Liverpool Street, London Bridge or into London's West End.

fields.transit: There are a number of options to get to the flat, the Overground being the fastest. The station is about ten minutes walk from the flat and the Overground will whisk you to Liverpool Street station in ten minutes with many popular spots like Bethnal Green and Hackney Downs along the way. In the other direction, Seven Sisters is only two Overground stops away, from where you can switch to the Underground Victoria Line to take you swiftly into the city. There are also a number of buses, such as Nos. 73 and 389 which will take you to Angel or Kings Cross or closer in, to Manor House station or Caledonian Road on the Piccadilly Line, the latter being preferable if you are arriving from Heathrow with baggage.

fields.host_about:
I would describe myself as quiet, compassionate and considerate. My daily regime includes yoga and Buddhist chanting, though I am not obsessive about it when on holiday. Five things I can't live without: my pot of green tea in the mornings, my NUJ membership, my Canon 650D, my moisturiser and my MacBook Pro. I am very eclectic in my tastes in music, books and food. My style of travelling can vary from luxury to backpacking, but I derive more pleasure from the latter. 
My idea of hosting is to make the guest feel as much at home as possible. A comfortable bed, lighting, a local hand-drawn map, clean surroundings are important and whenever possible, a home-cooked meal.

fields.host_about:
Greetings from London! 
 
My name is Tom and along with my team I manage this collection of hand-picked apartments and houses for their individual owners while they are away. Each property is carefully selected and offers a stylish living experience and excellent value. 

As a lifelong Londoner I love having the opportunity to share these spaces, my knowledge and personal recommendations about this great city with those visiting for both short and long term stays. 

All our guests will be greeted personally at the property by a member of our hospitality team, and guest assistance is also provided by our professional customer service team between 8am - 8pm 7 days a week, should any issues arise during your stay. Please note that once a booking is made, the customer service team will be the point of contact thereafter.

Please be aware that viewings are not possible for stays of less than 1 month.
  
If you have any questions please do not hesitate to contact me and I will be sure to answer them promptly.

fields.neighborhood_overview: The space is located between the borders of Dalston & Stoke Newington, a couple of minutes walk from Stoke Newington High street and Kingsland Road. There are few places in London that offer the zest, charm and charisma of Stoke Newington. Church Street is the area's lively epicentre, with packed-out bars and pubs never too far away. Stokie's shops overflow with indie labels and vintage goods and its restaurants are noteworthy for their diversity as well as their quality. Of course much of N16's success is down to the remarkably strong presence of independent business in the area, making it a truly distinctive part of the capital. You are also 10 minute walk from Clissold Park which is one of Hackneys best loved traditional parks with deers and farm animals.

Step out of the flat and you will find tones cafes, French bakery, English and Irish pubs, Italian / Spanish / Indian / Turkish and gastro pub restaurants and tonnes of independent stores. You will also find a butcher, fish monger, fruit & veg shop, florists and a spooky cemetery on church street  - Clissold park with playground, paddling pool, skate park, Table tennis tables, Tennis courts, butterfly dome, large animal enclosure including deer, goats and chicken ! only few minutes from the flat - The famous Dalston with hundreds of bars/clubs
fields.notes: Our bloc of flat is really friendly . People usually hang out outside for drinks or BBQ. Please tell us a bit about you when you make your booking !

fields.host_about:
Hello
Ciaran and I live in London . I'm French and he's Irish . Ciaran runs a bike shop and I work in fashion . We love travelling and usually use Airbnb when we go on an adventure ! 

We have a spare room in our family flat that we put on Airbnb when we don't have friends or family staying with us .

We also manage our friends and family amazing apartments in Stoke Newington when they are away . Check out our different listings!
